      <section eId="sec_CCP-1731">
        <num>CCP 1731</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1731__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as limited by Article 1732, the right of trial by jury is recognized.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1731__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as otherwise provided, the nature and amount of the principal demand shall determine whether any issue in the principal or incidental demand is triable by jury.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-1731__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the compulsory reconventional demand is triable by a jury, but the principal demand is not, the compulsory reconventional demand may be tried by a jury.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111289</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
